flowRoot.flowPara: To record and play sounds digitally. (cards: co2, t10, t12) You can change pitch, bass, trebles, snip single words and glue them together like you want. It is also possible to use other mathematical models, e.g. Fourier analysis/transform to analyse the samples or to modify them. Simplest variant, if you play twice the same with delay of 0.2 seconds to achieve an echo effect. If you create a physical models of human voice you could even fade between 2 different voices (see t21 card) To make music, manipulate voice recordings prior to negotiation, behavioral sciences, e.g. The "Pavlovian Dog" experiment... but also a very cool kids toy.
